---
import { type Lang } from "@/i18n"

type Props = { lang: Lang }
const { lang } = Astro.props
---

<prose-content>
  {lang === "zh" ? (
    <>
      <h1>关于</h1>
      <p>我有个毛病:外面变得越快,我越得把某件事彻底搞清楚,才睡得着觉。</p>
      <p>
        别人说"这次不一样了",我第一反应不是兴奋,是难受——到底哪里不一样?变了多少?数据真这么说吗?这种悬空的感觉我受不了。所以我钻进数据里,把一件事到底发生了什么弄明白,钉死。「枢」是门轴:世界在转,我想知道它到底绕着什么转。把那个轴找出来,我自己才站得稳一点。
      </p>
      <p>
        这里的文章基本都是这么写出来的。每一篇都会给一个明确的判断,有时候听着像暴论——但底下都垫着数据,不是情绪。
      </p>
      <p>
        我不写那种"某种程度上有其合理性"的文章。那不是分析,是买保险。想清楚了我才发,发了就把话说死;对就对,错就认。
      </p>
      <p>
        如果你也老觉得脚下的地在晃,想找几块还算结实的石头踩——进来坐。订阅 <a href="/zh/rss.xml">RSS</a>,或读 <a href="/about">English</a>。
      </p>
    </>
  ) : (
    <>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>
        I've got a tic: the faster the world outside moves, the more I need to
        get one thing completely straight before I can sleep.
      </p>
      <p>
        When someone says "this time it's different," my first reaction isn't
        excitement — it's unease. Different how? By how much? Is that really
        what the data says? I can't stand that floating feeling. So I dig into
        the data until I know what actually happened, and I nail it down. 枢
        means the pivot of a door: the world turns, and I want to know what it's
        turning around. Find that pivot, and I stand a little steadier myself.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's how almost everything here gets written. Every piece lands a
        definite call — sometimes it sounds like a hot take, but there's always
        data under it, not mood.
      </p>
      <p>
        I don't write the "there's arguably some merit to it" kind of piece.
        That's not analysis, it's buying insurance. I post only once I've
        thought it through, and then I say it flat out: right is right, and if
        I'm wrong I'll own it.
      </p>
      <p>
        If the ground under you always feels like it's shifting, and you want a
        few solid stones to stand on — pull up a chair. Subscribe via
        <a href="/rss.xml"> RSS</a>, or read in <a href="/zh/about">中文</a>.
      </p>
    </>
  )}
</prose-content>
